The finding pertains to the verbose error handling present on the application which results in information being exposed to users that could potentially be useful to an attacker (such as stack traces, file paths, server information, etc.).

The fix is to disable verbose error handling such that users of the site are only presented with vague error messages that do not expose information that could be useful to an attacker. If such information needs to be logged, it should be kept on the server and not exposed to the user

